[[cdo:3 nguŏk 15 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:3 goe̍h 15 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:三月十五]] {{Lunisolar March}} '''March 15''' is the 15th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|12=draft}}.
== Events == * [[太康 (晋)|太康]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[280]] {{ill|May 1|ja|5月1日}}) – In this year, the grandson Hao of Wu surrendered to the Jin, leading to the unification of China under Jin. * [[Gangyō]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[878]] {{ill|April 21|ja|4月21日}}) – The Gangyō Rebellion occurred in Dewa, when a revolt by the Ezo erupted and attacked Akita Castle. * [[Keichō]] 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1598]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日}}) – A famed flower-viewing event was held at Daigo. Toyotomi Hideyoshi and Hideyori had their final hanami. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 7|ja|4月7日}}) – The Meiji government established high-ranking signboards known as the "Gobō no Keiji" at the outset of its reforms.
== Births == * [[Keichō]] 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1606]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日}}) – {{ill|Nanbu Shigenao|ja|南部重直}}, the 2nd lord of the Morioka Domain (died [[1664]]). * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft}} 20th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1735]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日}}) – {{ill|Katō Chien|ja|加藤千蔭}}, a Kokugaku scholar and waka poet (died [[1808]]).
== Deaths == * [[履中天皇]] 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[405]] {{ill|April 29|ja|4月29日}}) – {{ill|Emperor Ritsuchū|ja|履中天皇}}, the 17th Emperor of Japan.
