{{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 15''' is the 15th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|qq=}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Taikang|ja|太康_(晋)|zh|太康_(西晋)|ko|태강_(서진)|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[280]] {{ill|May 1|ja|5月1日|qq=}}) – In this year, the grandson Hao of Wu surrendered to the Jin, leading to the unification of China under Jin. * [[Gangyō]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[878]] {{ill|April 21|ja|4月21日|qq=}}) – The Gangyō Rebellion occurred in Dewa, when a revolt by the Ezo erupted and attacked Akita Castle. * [[Keichō]] 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1598]] {{ill|April 20|ja|4月20日|qq=}}) – A famed flower-viewing event was held at Daigo. Toyotomi Hideyoshi and Hideyori had their final hanami. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 7|ja|4月7日|qq=}}) – The Meiji government established high-Ranking signboards known as the "Gobō no Keiji" at the outset of its reforms.
== Births == * [[Keichō]] 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1606]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Nanbu Shigenao|ja|南部重直|qq=}}, the 2nd lord of the Morioka Domain (died [[1664]]). * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|qq=}} 20th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} [[1735]] {{ill|April 1|ja|4月1日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Katō Chien|ja|加藤千蔭|qq=}}, a Kokugaku scholar and waka poet (died [[1808]]).
== Deaths == * [[Emperor Richū]] 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} [[405]] {{ill|April 29|ja|4月29日|qq=}}) – {{ill|Emperor Ritsuchū|ja|履中天皇|qq=}}, the 17th Emperor of Japan.
