== Events == * {{ill|Taikang|ja|太康_(晋)|zh|太康_(西晋)|ko|태강_(서진)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taikang|qq=}} 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:280|280]] [[:en:May 1|May 1]]) – In this year, the grandson Hao of Wu surrendered to the Jin, leading to the unification of China under Jin. * [[Gangyō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[878]] [[:en:April 21|April 21]]) – The Gangyō Rebellion occurred in Dewa, when a revolt by the Ezo erupted and attacked Akita Castle. * [[Keichō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1598|1598]] [[:en:April 20|April 20]]) – A famed flower-viewing event was held at Daigo. Toyotomi Hideyoshi and Hideyori had their final hanami. * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:April 7|April 7]]) – The Meiji government established high-Ranking signboards known as the "Gobō no Keiji" at the outset of its reforms.
== Births == * [[Keichō]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1606|1606]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – [[:en:Nanbu Shigenao|Nanbu Shigenao]], the 2nd lord of the Morioka Domain (died [[:en:1664|1664]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 20th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1735|1735]] [[:en:April 1|April 1]]) – {{ill|Katō Chien|ja|加藤千蔭|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katō Chien|qq=}}, a Kokugaku scholar and waka poet (died [[:en:1808|1808]]).
== Deaths == * [[Emperor Richū]] 6th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:405|405]] [[:en:April 29|April 29]]) – [[:en:Emperor Richū|Emperor Ritsuchū]], the 17th Emperor of Japan.
