'''March 15''' is the 15th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|qid=Q96759844|1=taian}}{{efn|ja|大安|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|1=taian|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q1306255}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Taikang|ja|太康_(晋)|zh|太康_(西晋)|ko|태강_(서진)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taikang|1=Taikang|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q8011632}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|280|en|280|qid=Q32237|lt=280|1=280}} {{ill|May 1|en|May 1|qid=Q2544|lt=May 1|1=May 1}}) – In this year, the grandson Hao of Wu surrendered to the Jin, leading to the unification of China under Jin.
* {{ill|Gangyō|en|Gangyō|qid=Q747451|lt=Gangyō|1=Gangyō}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|878|en|878|qid=Q23910|lt=878|1=878}} {{ill|April 21|en|April 21|qid=Q2525|lt=April 21|1=April 21}}) – The Gangyō Rebellion occurred in Dewa, when a revolt by the Ezo erupted and attacked Akita Castle.
* {{ill|Keichō|en|Keichō|qid=Q1328185|lt=Keichō|1=Keichō}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1598|en|1598|qid=Q6800|lt=1598|1=1598}} {{ill|April 20|en|April 20|qid=Q2524|lt=April 20|1=April 20}}) – A famed flower-viewing event was held at Daigo. Toyotomi Hideyoshi and Hideyori had their final hanami.
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji|1=Meiji era}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1868|en|1868|qid=Q7717|lt=1868|1=1868}} {{ill|April 7|en|April 7|qid=Q2505|lt=April 7|1=April 7}}) – The Meiji government established high-Ranking signboards known as the "Gobō no Keiji" at the outset of its reforms.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Keichō|en|Keichō|qid=Q1328185|lt=Keichō|1=Keichō}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1606|en|1606|qid=Q6747|lt=1606|1=1606}} {{ill|April 16|en|April 16|qid=Q2519|lt=April 16|1=April 16}}) – {{ill|Nanbu Shigenao|en|Nanbu Shigenao|qid=Q6962458|lt=Nanbu Shigenao|1=Nanbu Shigenao}}, the 2nd lord of the Morioka Domain (died {{ill|1664|en|1664|qid=Q7581|lt=1664|1=1664}}).
* {{ill|Kyōhō|en|Kyōhō|qid=Q1145048|lt=Kyōhō|1=Kyōhō}} 20th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1735|en|1735|qid=Q6984|lt=1735|1=1735}} {{ill|April 1|en|April 1|qid=Q2510|lt=April 1|1=April 1}}) – {{ill|Katō Chien|ja|加藤千蔭|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katō Chien|1=Katō Chikage|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q1293828}}, a Kokugaku scholar and waka poet (died {{ill|1808|en|1808|qid=Q6914|lt=1808|1=1808}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Emperor Richū|en|Emperor Richū|qid=Q329704|lt=Emperor Richū|1=Emperor Richū}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|405|en|405|qid=Q32745|lt=405|1=405}} {{ill|April 29|en|April 29|qid=Q2535|lt=April 29|1=April 29}}) – {{ill|Emperor Richū|en|Emperor Richū|qid=Q329704|lt=Emperor Ritsuchū|1=Emperor Richū}}, the 17th Emperor of Japan.

